<i>♪ When the lights go out ♪</i>

13:05.125 --> 13:06.833
<i>♪ Who will be there? ♪</i>

13:06.916 --> 13:09.916
<i>♪ Who will be there for us? ♪</i>

13:10.000 --> 13:12.958
<i>♪ When the lights go out ♪</i>

13:13.041 --> 13:14.958
<i>♪ Who will be there? ♪</i>

13:15.041 --> 13:17.458
<i>♪ Who will be there for us? ♪</i>

13:20.500 --> 13:23.708
<i>♪ Tell me all your secrets ♪</i>

13:23.791 --> 13:28.291
<i>♪ And I'll tell you none of mine ♪</i>

13:28.375 --> 13:30.583
-[horn honks]
-<i>♪ Into my arms come now ♪</i>

13:30.666 --> 13:34.625
<i>♪ Then wish you never had ♪</i>

13:36.333 --> 13:39.250
<i>♪ The struggle is in vain ♪</i>

13:39.333 --> 13:43.875
<i>♪ You will succumb to my embrace ♪</i>

13:44.708 --> 13:47.625
<i>♪ Hands up in the air ♪</i>

13:47.708 --> 13:52.166
<i>♪ Oh, surrender ♪</i>

13:52.250 --> 13:55.041
<i>♪ When the lights go out ♪</i>

13:55.125 --> 13:56.791
<i>♪ Who will be there? ♪</i>

13:56.875 --> 13:59.875
<i>♪ Who will be there for us? ♪</i>

13:59.958 --> 14:02.666
<i>♪ When the lights go out ♪</i>

14:02.750 --> 14:04.875
<i>♪ Who will be there? ♪</i>

14:04.958 --> 14:07.916
<i>♪ Who will be there for us? ♪</i>

14:08.000 --> 14:11.166
<i>♪ When the lights go out ♪</i>

14:11.250 --> 14:13.000
<i>♪ Who will be there? ♪</i>

14:17.125 --> 14:19.125
[upbeat music]

14:19.875 --> 14:20.833
Hey.

14:21.291 --> 14:22.666
Sunglasses at night.

14:22.750 --> 14:24.125
[chuckles]
That's new.

14:24.208 --> 14:25.208
[sighs]

14:25.875 --> 14:27.416
What's wrong, Ngozi?

14:30.541 --> 14:32.708
Huh, who did that to you?

14:33.083 --> 14:34.541
My employer.

14:34.625 --> 14:36.291
What? Why?

14:37.000 --> 14:38.250
Because of you.

14:38.333 --> 14:39.333
Me?

14:41.291 --> 14:44.750
You work in banking,
why would that have to--

14:47.000 --> 14:48.000
[scoffs]

14:49.833 --> 14:51.416
You don't work in banking.

14:54.000 --> 14:56.166
I work for Obicorps Pharmaceuticals.

14:56.250 --> 14:59.833
Obicorp, they are an applicant
for the contract I'm awarding.

15:00.083 --> 15:01.375
They are not happy.

15:02.541 --> 15:06.583
And they thought I would award
a million-dollar contract for you.

15:07.500 --> 15:08.500
[scoffs]

15:09.041 --> 15:11.041
They must think you're really special.

15:14.666 --> 15:16.458
It wasn't just a job for me.

15:26.083 --> 15:27.583
I had to ask them.

15:29.916 --> 15:32.750
Thank you, and I... I really am sorry.

15:35.500 --> 15:36.583
Wait.

15:43.958 --> 15:45.083
I'll do it.

15:46.083 --> 15:48.666
[light music playing]

15:51.833 --> 15:54.250
-[Dimeji] I can't get enough of you.
-[Grace gasps]

15:54.333 --> 15:56.000
[Grace] Yes, Daddy.
[laughs]

15:56.083 --> 15:56.958
[Grace] Wow.

15:57.041 --> 15:58.500
Thou art in such a hurry.

15:58.583 --> 15:59.958
[Dimeji] Oh, yes, I am.

16:00.083 --> 16:01.291
[Grace] Welcome, baby.

16:01.375 --> 16:02.541
[Dimeji and Grace laugh]

16:04.958 --> 16:05.958
[Dimeji] Hmm.

16:06.708 --> 16:07.708
[Grace] Ah.

16:08.041 --> 16:09.291
[Dimeji] So where were we?

16:09.375 --> 16:11.791
[Dimeji sighs heavily]

16:12.041 --> 16:13.125
Mm.
[smooches]

16:14.166 --> 16:15.208
[Grace] Okay.

16:15.833 --> 16:17.125
Jesus!

16:17.541 --> 16:19.208
-I think I've seen enough.
-[chuckles]

16:23.000 --> 16:24.500
Who are you and what are you doing in my--

16:24.583 --> 16:25.666
In your room?

16:26.750 --> 16:29.541
Well, Pastor Dimeji, I'm your friend.

16:30.916 --> 16:32.375
[Chike] Isn't that right, Tayo?

16:32.458 --> 16:33.750
Yes, it is.

16:40.833 --> 16:42.166
What, what is this?

16:42.250 --> 16:43.125
[clicks tongue]

16:43.208 --> 16:45.666
This... is a camera.

16:46.666 --> 16:47.666
[clicks tongue]

16:54.833 --> 16:55.958
What do you want?

16:58.166 --> 16:59.375
Uh-oh.

17:00.541 --> 17:02.250
[Grace] I'll leave you guys to it.

17:18.583 --> 17:20.416
Must you eat that now?

17:23.833 --> 17:24.958
[clears throat]

17:27.833 --> 17:29.125
Chike is here.

17:37.708 --> 17:39.000
Did something happen?

17:39.083 --> 17:40.125
Report.

17:40.208 --> 17:41.291
Oh, it's done.

17:41.375 --> 17:44.125
You can tell Megapharma that the Pastor
will no longer be a problem.

17:44.791 --> 17:47.791
[light music]

17:50.583 --> 17:51.708
[Chike] <i>What's wrong?</i>

17:53.500 --> 17:55.041
Are you feeling bad about Dimeji?

17:55.458 --> 17:57.208
I told you not to fall for him.

17:57.458 --> 17:58.458
No.

17:59.375 --> 18:00.750
It's not Dimeji.

18:02.125 --> 18:03.416
Megapharma.

18:04.333 --> 18:05.458
[sighs]

18:05.541 --> 18:10.083
Chike, Megapharma is testing
unauthorized drugs on children.

18:11.708 --> 18:12.666
[sighs]

18:13.791 --> 18:15.666
[stutters]
Why are we...

18:15.750 --> 18:18.333
[sighs]
Why are we letting this happen?

18:18.875 --> 18:20.500
Okay, what would you have me do?

18:22.750 --> 18:25.041
Chike, we can run away, we can go.

18:25.125 --> 18:26.750
With all Madame knows about us?

18:27.166 --> 18:29.958
Do you want to spend the rest of your life
running from the NDLEA?

18:31.625 --> 18:33.166
What about what we know about her?

18:33.750 --> 18:35.250
We can bring her down.

18:37.750 --> 18:40.708
Come on, Chike,
is this the life you want to live?

18:42.083 --> 18:43.750
Seducing pastors

18:43.833 --> 18:45.958
and blackmailing them
into not whistleblowing

18:46.041 --> 18:48.958
on a pharmaceutical company,
testing wrong drugs,

18:49.625 --> 18:52.125
or fooling and deceiving
young trade attaché's

18:52.208 --> 18:55.875
into making millions
for secret government contractors.

18:55.958 --> 18:57.291
Is that what you want?

18:59.000 --> 19:00.291
-I thought--
-Grace.

19:00.708 --> 19:03.333
Technically, you seduced the pastor.

19:06.833 --> 19:07.875
Chike...

19:08.458 --> 19:10.541
-we don't have to live like this.
-[clicks tongue]

19:11.458 --> 19:13.333
-We can go.
-Mm.

19:13.666 --> 19:16.625
You know that if your dad was alive,
he will not do this.

19:16.708 --> 19:17.791
Well, he's dead.

19:17.875 --> 19:20.041
-So he doesn't get a say, does he?
-[scoffs]

19:23.375 --> 19:24.791
-Okay.
-[knocks on door]

19:24.875 --> 19:26.458
-[door opens]
-[Madame] Oh, good.

19:26.541 --> 19:27.708
[Madame] You're awake.

19:28.666 --> 19:30.000
We have a guest.

19:30.083 --> 19:31.750
So, you dress up.

19:31.833 --> 19:33.541
Make it simple, wear glasses.

19:34.000 --> 19:35.166
Leave the red band.

19:39.500 --> 19:41.041
We'll talk about this later.

19:42.500 --> 19:43.708
The good stuff.

19:44.041 --> 19:45.083
Mm-hm.

19:45.541 --> 19:46.750
How you spoil me.

19:58.208 --> 20:00.916
She... is perfect.

20:03.416 --> 20:05.500
[Edem] <i>Motunrayo Elesho.</i>

20:07.125 --> 20:09.500
[Chike] <i>Motunrayo Elesho, the socialite?</i>

20:09.583 --> 20:11.208
-I want to marry her.
-[scoffs]

20:11.583 --> 20:13.625
Uh, that's ambitious.

20:14.208 --> 20:16.958
Oh, I like this one.
[chuckles]

20:17.416 --> 20:18.875
Tunde Elesho.

20:19.541 --> 20:21.916
The founder of Diageo bank.

20:22.250 --> 20:25.500
[Edem] <i>One day at 60,
he drops dead of a heart attack.</i>

20:28.875 --> 20:30.875
<i>He leaves everything to his children.</i>

20:30.958 --> 20:32.083
<i>Everything...</i>

20:32.625 --> 20:34.875
<i>He also left his wife as chairman.</i>

20:36.041 --> 20:38.333
[Chike] <i>You think she is looking
for a father figure?</i>

20:39.250 --> 20:41.000
[Edem] <i>Which bad girl isn't?</i>

20:41.833 --> 20:43.708
[sighs]
[Chike] <i>So what's the in?</i>

20:44.250 --> 20:46.083
[Edem] <i>Her father's memorial...</i>

20:47.125 --> 20:49.458
<i>is next month, his 10th memorial.</i>

20:53.166 --> 20:54.625
<i>That's when we make our move.</i>

21:10.708 --> 21:11.791
[clears throat]

21:15.083 --> 21:16.833
I know exactly how you feel.

21:18.083 --> 21:20.416
-Uncle Edem.
-[both laugh]

21:20.500 --> 21:22.458
So you finally decided to show up.

21:23.541 --> 21:25.041
Is that the welcome I get?

21:25.708 --> 21:29.333
I haven't seen you in years,
what kind of welcome were you expecting?

21:29.416 --> 21:33.541
Now, I was expecting something
a little warmer perhaps.

21:34.375 --> 21:36.708
Listen, I know it seems--

21:38.750 --> 21:40.166
What are you doing here?

21:44.041 --> 21:45.208
[sighs]

21:46.458 --> 21:48.416
It is good to see you too, Toyin.

21:49.083 --> 21:52.625
What are you doing here?

21:54.666 --> 21:56.458
I came to pay my respects.

21:59.000 --> 22:00.416
You're not welcome here.

22:01.875 --> 22:02.958
Leave.

22:04.791 --> 22:07.166
Toyin, it doesn't always have to...

22:08.166 --> 22:09.916
Would you rather I call security?

22:18.000 --> 22:19.208
[Edem sighs]

22:20.666 --> 22:22.833
[tense music]

22:28.625 --> 22:29.916
[Chike] <i>You know them.</i>

22:30.166 --> 22:31.500
And you didn't think to mention this

22:31.583 --> 22:33.416
in the entire month
we were working on this?

22:33.833 --> 22:35.708
It wouldn't have helped you to know.

22:35.791 --> 22:37.000
It wouldn't have helped to know

22:37.083 --> 22:38.750
that you had a prior relationship
with a mark.

22:38.833 --> 22:39.958
Are you crazy?

22:40.958 --> 22:43.041
How did you know I was there
in the first place?

22:43.375 --> 22:44.708
What are you talking about?

22:46.166 --> 22:49.291
You were supposed to make contact
with the target at the club, right?

22:49.666 --> 22:51.250
And I still plan to.

22:52.458 --> 22:54.750
So how did you know I was there?

22:58.041 --> 23:00.000
You had someone there, didn't you?

23:01.041 --> 23:02.041
Huh?

23:02.125 --> 23:04.166
Seems both of us broke the rules.

23:04.458 --> 23:05.375
Enough.

23:07.458 --> 23:09.208
[Grace] <i>And Madame never said anything?</i>

23:09.333 --> 23:10.708
[Chike] Not a thing.

23:11.875 --> 23:14.583
[Grace] So, is that why you want us
to meet here where we won't be overheard?

23:14.666 --> 23:16.333
Are you worried about Madame?

23:17.166 --> 23:20.041
Edem says he's known Madame
for over 20 years.

23:20.500 --> 23:23.791
I want to know how they know each other
and why she let him pull that crap.

23:25.000 --> 23:27.833
Is that all you want me to do,
or would you like me to walk on water too?

23:27.916 --> 23:29.583
-[mumbling]
-[scoffs]

23:30.291 --> 23:31.458
If you must.

23:32.916 --> 23:34.708
<i>♪ Otedola with the money ♪</i>

23:35.333 --> 23:36.916
<i>♪ Jim Iyke with the love ♪</i>

23:37.791 --> 23:39.166
<i>♪ Okocha with the ball ♪</i>

23:39.958 --> 23:41.375
<i>♪ Maggi with the sause ♪</i>

23:41.958 --> 23:44.291
<i>♪ Otedola with the money, oooh ♪</i>

23:44.375 --> 23:46.083
<i>♪ Ramsey Noah with the love ♪</i>

23:46.500 --> 23:48.458
<i>♪ Okocha with the balling, oooh ♪</i>

23:48.541 --> 23:50.291
<i>♪ Ajenomoto with the sause, eh ♪</i>

23:50.375 --> 23:53.125
<i>♪ My girl coke bottle in the body, oh ♪</i>

23:53.208 --> 23:54.583
<i>♪ Coke bottle in the body ♪</i>

23:55.750 --> 23:58.875
<i>♪ Coke bottle in the body, oh
You go kill somebody ♪</i>

23:59.125 --> 24:01.958
<i>♪ My girl coke bottle in the body, oh ♪</i>

24:02.041 --> 24:03.375
<i>♪ Coke bottle in the body ♪</i>

24:04.500 --> 24:07.583
<i>♪ Coke bottle in the body, oh
You go kill somebody ♪</i>

24:07.666 --> 24:09.666
<i>♪ All my girl so bad, they be foreign ♪</i>

24:09.750 --> 24:12.416
<i>♪ Kim with the body
Rihanna with the face ♪</i>

24:13.250 --> 24:16.291
[Chike] Good evening, ma.
Should I open it?

24:16.375 --> 24:17.833
Sure, open it.

24:18.083 --> 24:20.833
<i>♪ She be fanta with e color, oh
Honey with the taste ♪</i>

24:21.708 --> 24:25.208
<i>♪ Vanilla with the flavor
Shakira with the waist ♪</i>

24:25.291 --> 24:26.208
Okay.

24:28.708 --> 24:30.666
Do I look like an amateur?

24:30.750 --> 24:32.000
We are a go.

24:36.541 --> 24:37.500
Yeah.

24:38.041 --> 24:39.375
It's time, it's time.

24:44.875 --> 24:48.708
[guns clicking]

24:50.500 --> 24:52.666
[in Pidgin]
Sir, what, what is the problem?

24:53.333 --> 24:55.083
[in English]
This car is a stolen car.

24:55.166 --> 24:56.666
Ah, this car a stolen car?

24:56.750 --> 24:57.958
-Yes!
-It's not possible.

24:58.041 --> 24:59.250
This car is a stolen car, Mr. Man.

24:59.333 --> 25:00.958
-It's not a stolen car, sir.
-Okay.

25:01.041 --> 25:02.375
Do you know who you are talking about?

25:02.458 --> 25:04.125
-I don't care who the person is.
-Excuse me.

25:04.583 --> 25:06.416
Officer, what seems to be the problem?

25:06.750 --> 25:08.541
Ma, this car is a stolen car.

25:08.833 --> 25:10.041
-This car?
-Yes.

25:10.458 --> 25:11.708
You don't know what...

25:12.250 --> 25:15.208
-This car is not stolen.
-It was reported stolen, madam.

25:15.666 --> 25:17.083
-You must be mistaken,
-Hold it, just...

25:17.166 --> 25:18.416
it's not a stolen car.

25:19.541 --> 25:21.583
[phone beeping]

25:24.958 --> 25:26.708
-[busy tone]
-[Motunrayo groans]

25:26.791 --> 25:29.291
-[phone chiming]
-[indistinct chatter]

25:31.083 --> 25:32.291
-[Motunrayo] Hello?
-[phone static]

25:33.375 --> 25:34.416
[Motunrayo] Hello?

25:35.708 --> 25:37.708
[indistinct chatter]

25:38.625 --> 25:41.500
[driver] You asked I move, I'll move back.
Officer, you are playing with your job.

25:41.583 --> 25:43.291
-Officer, please.
-[officer] Get me a towing van!

25:43.375 --> 25:45.375
-[driver] This... this is...
-You can't tow this car, oh.

25:45.458 --> 25:46.375
[Motunrayo] This is wrong.

25:46.458 --> 25:47.708
You can't be doing this.

25:47.791 --> 25:49.541
[officer] Come back, come back.

25:49.625 --> 25:51.291
How can my car be stolen? It's not stolen.

25:51.375 --> 25:53.125
What the fuck is wrong with my phone?

25:53.208 --> 25:55.291
[indistinct chatter]

25:55.375 --> 25:56.958
[beeps]

25:59.250 --> 26:00.875
-[beeping]
-[Motunrayo] Oh, shit!

26:02.791 --> 26:03.750
Damn it!

26:03.833 --> 26:05.083
[Chike] Are you okay?

26:08.541 --> 26:09.583
You.

26:10.041 --> 26:11.291
[laughs]

26:12.250 --> 26:14.250
Can I borrow your phone?

26:14.333 --> 26:15.541
My phone is dead.

26:17.083 --> 26:18.750
Can I borrow some money?

26:19.000 --> 26:20.125
What money?

26:20.291 --> 26:23.458
I'll have to beg my landlord
to take late rent again.

26:25.083 --> 26:27.166
I'm hoping the remaining 500 naira I have,

26:27.250 --> 26:29.250
is enough to buy petrol to take me home.

26:31.791 --> 26:33.208
Look...
[sighs]

26:33.750 --> 26:36.416
You have a car, I'll pay your rent.

26:36.500 --> 26:37.625
If you take me home.

26:37.708 --> 26:38.583
What?

26:38.875 --> 26:39.875
I bet that's stupid.

26:39.958 --> 26:41.916
Go into the club
and ask someone to help you.

26:43.416 --> 26:45.166
-[indistinct chatter in Yoruba]
-Um...

26:45.250 --> 26:50.541
[indistinct chatter in Yoruba continues]

26:51.041 --> 26:53.000
Please, I have money.

26:53.083 --> 26:55.541
It's my money, I'll pay you what you want.

26:59.583 --> 27:03.833
[indistinct chatter]

27:03.916 --> 27:10.708
-[tires screech]
-[indistinct chatter]

27:11.250 --> 27:15.375
[chatter in Yoruba]

27:15.458 --> 27:16.750
[in Yoruba]
Keep quiet.

27:16.833 --> 27:18.041
[in Yoruba]
Do you know her?

27:18.125 --> 27:21.916
Are you mad?

27:22.958 --> 27:25.041
[in Yoruba]
This is the most important thing.

27:25.125 --> 27:26.333
[chuckles]

27:26.416 --> 27:28.166
[in Yoruba]
Money is the most important thing.

27:28.250 --> 27:30.458
[speaking Yoruba]

27:33.541 --> 27:34.833
[Chike] Your phone is working.

27:35.583 --> 27:37.083
-[Motunrayo] What?
-[Chike] Your phone.

27:37.416 --> 27:38.458
[Chike] It's working.

27:39.041 --> 27:40.875
[Motunrayo] Oh, my god. Yes, it is.

27:41.958 --> 27:43.583
[Chike] You don't need me anymore.

27:44.083 --> 27:46.125
You can order an Uber or whatever.

27:50.541 --> 27:51.583
[Motunrayo sighs]

27:52.083 --> 27:53.208
[Motunrayo] You know what?

27:53.291 --> 27:54.458
We had a deal.

27:54.750 --> 27:56.750
You take me home and I pay your rent.

28:00.541 --> 28:02.333
[Chike] I need to stop at home briefly.

28:09.750 --> 28:11.416
[Motunrayo] You live here?

28:12.291 --> 28:13.958
You have no idea.

28:15.083 --> 28:16.041
Uh.

28:20.708 --> 28:21.750
Please, I'm coming.

28:21.833 --> 28:22.708
Okay.

28:22.791 --> 28:24.416
-I'll be right back.
-All right.

28:32.333 --> 28:34.625
Oh...
[chuckles]

28:38.125 --> 28:39.375
-[groans]
-[lock clanks]

28:42.916 --> 28:45.458
[Chike] Oh, I can't believe
that this guy...

28:45.541 --> 28:47.208
-[dog barking]
-...locked my house.

28:47.750 --> 28:49.333
I can't believe
that this guy locked my house.

28:49.416 --> 28:51.125
God help me punish, Mr. Edem.

28:51.208 --> 28:52.333
God will punish him.

28:55.000 --> 28:56.833
He locked my house.

28:56.916 --> 28:58.750
He actually used padlocks.

29:01.458 --> 29:02.708
[Chike] Mr. Edem!

29:03.916 --> 29:05.166
Mr. Edem!

29:06.208 --> 29:07.958
Mr. Edem, this is not fair!

29:08.583 --> 29:12.041
Mr. Edem, why will you lock my house now?
Mr. Edem, it's not fair!

29:14.625 --> 29:17.708
Mr. Edem, it's not...
Why did you padlock my house?

29:18.750 --> 29:20.166
I got your message.

29:22.166 --> 29:23.125
Okay?

29:23.750 --> 29:24.875
I'm done.

29:24.958 --> 29:26.083
I'm tired of this.

29:26.166 --> 29:27.625
-You--
-[Edem] No, no. I'm not hearing it.

29:27.708 --> 29:28.541
We're done.

29:28.625 --> 29:30.750
I need you to get your stuff,
first thing tomorrow.

29:31.291 --> 29:32.125
That's it.

29:32.250 --> 29:33.791
-Ah, Mr. Ed--
-[Edem] No, no. No, seriously,

29:33.875 --> 29:35.666
-I'm done with you.
-[Motunrayo] Uncle Edem?

29:38.916 --> 29:39.958
Motunrayo.

29:41.333 --> 29:42.708
What are you doing here?

29:43.416 --> 29:44.625
And with her?

29:45.916 --> 29:47.875
Uh... she's...

29:48.166 --> 29:49.125
a friend.

29:50.416 --> 29:53.291
-And, and I'm here to help pay her rent.
-Hm.

29:54.041 --> 29:55.000
Right.

29:55.625 --> 29:56.625
Okay.

29:57.333 --> 29:58.375
Come in.

30:04.458 --> 30:05.708
[Chike] Sorry, ma.

30:11.458 --> 30:12.958
Thank you, Aunty.

30:19.625 --> 30:20.958
[Chike] Do you know them?

30:22.541 --> 30:26.458
That's my dad, Edem, and Aunt Enitan.

30:26.541 --> 30:27.916
My dad's former PA.

30:28.000 --> 30:31.041
[coughing]

30:31.125 --> 30:32.041
[sniffles]

30:36.083 --> 30:37.250
Well, hello there.

30:38.208 --> 30:39.375
How's it going?

30:39.458 --> 30:40.791
It's good.

30:41.541 --> 30:43.083
So what happened?

30:43.541 --> 30:45.708
You were gone for 13 years.

30:47.416 --> 30:52.291
Well, during the 2004 bank consolidation,

30:53.166 --> 30:55.875
I made a takeover bid
with a different investor.

30:56.250 --> 30:57.708
[chuckles]

30:57.791 --> 31:01.041
My dad would have rather died
than sell his company.

31:02.916 --> 31:04.583
I thought I was helping out.

31:05.500 --> 31:08.083
He, on the other hand,
thought it was a betrayal.

31:08.625 --> 31:12.708
Sorry, um, it's getting late,
and I'm working a double shift tomorrow.

31:13.041 --> 31:15.708
Oh, right, of course.

31:16.500 --> 31:18.208
Okay.
[clears throat]

31:23.916 --> 31:25.041
[sighs]

31:27.625 --> 31:29.375
-Hm.
-Thank you.

31:31.041 --> 31:32.291
-[Chike] Uh-uh.
-Okay, so.

31:32.666 --> 31:34.458
[Chike] No, but we had a deal, no, like,

31:34.541 --> 31:36.333
you pay my rent and I take you home.

31:36.875 --> 31:38.750
But my car is already here.

31:41.041 --> 31:42.291
[relieved sigh]

31:44.166 --> 31:46.458
-[Chike] Who is that?
-It's okay, he's my brother.

31:47.916 --> 31:49.208
Hey.

31:49.291 --> 31:50.750
-Thank you.
-What the hell, sis.

31:51.333 --> 31:52.458
It's 4:00 a.m.

31:53.625 --> 31:55.791
My car was impounded by the police.

31:55.875 --> 31:57.708
Yeah, it's always one thing or the other.

31:57.791 --> 31:58.958
Please, let's go.

32:00.083 --> 32:03.625
This is my baby brother Bamidele.

32:03.708 --> 32:06.833
Although with the way he's acting,
you can't really tell.

32:06.916 --> 32:08.166
This is Janet.

32:08.250 --> 32:09.125
Hello.

32:09.458 --> 32:12.333
Please get in the car,
let me drop you off and go back to bed.

32:14.125 --> 32:15.000
[sighs]

32:15.083 --> 32:16.416
Anyway, thank you.

32:16.500 --> 32:18.708
-Thank you. Bye.
-[chuckles]

32:30.416 --> 32:31.708
What are you doing?

32:32.166 --> 32:33.833
We had a plan.

32:35.833 --> 32:37.500
I changed the plans.

32:38.041 --> 32:41.083
We were supposed to be playing you
as a cooler, aloof older man.

32:41.458 --> 32:43.875
What is this, I'm the disgrace friend
of the family shit?

32:43.958 --> 32:45.708
How is that attractive to anybody?

32:47.125 --> 32:49.750
You know, I really don't need
to explain myself to anyone.

32:49.833 --> 32:53.500
Stop messing with my plan.

32:54.250 --> 32:56.291
I'll slap that stupid look off your face.

33:05.458 --> 33:06.625
[Chike] This is new.

33:07.458 --> 33:09.791
Are you hoping to bring
your boyfriend here?

33:11.000 --> 33:12.666
Dimeji doesn't come here.

33:13.166 --> 33:16.041
He feels bad about what's been done
to the children in his name.

33:16.375 --> 33:19.208
What's been done to these children
except play and free food.

33:19.625 --> 33:20.875
That boy over there.

33:21.250 --> 33:23.291
[Grace] He got the vaccination
less than a year ago.

33:23.375 --> 33:25.500
[Chike] How do you know he wasn't
in the wheelchair before?

33:25.583 --> 33:28.083
Because he was the case
I used to find Dimeji.

33:28.166 --> 33:30.583
That boy was one of the brightest kids
in this orphanage.

33:30.666 --> 33:32.916
Grace, this isn't our problem.

33:33.000 --> 33:34.166
We need to focus.

33:34.250 --> 33:36.875
Chike, I cannot even understand
how you're not bothered.

33:36.958 --> 33:38.041
We're not the ones doing it.

33:38.125 --> 33:39.541
But we're letting them do it.

33:39.625 --> 33:40.791
Grace, I get it.

33:40.875 --> 33:42.791
You like Pastor Dimeji,
you like these children,

33:42.875 --> 33:44.708
and what's happening to them is a tragedy.

33:44.791 --> 33:46.333
But, Grace, this isn't our fight.

33:46.416 --> 33:48.083
We could make it our fight.

33:51.125 --> 33:52.333
You called.

33:53.041 --> 33:55.833
Now, do you have anything on the Enitan
that worked for Daraja?

33:59.000 --> 34:00.083
Thank you.

34:04.500 --> 34:07.041
[gloomy music]

34:10.791 --> 34:11.958
[gasps]

34:12.583 --> 34:14.583
You've got to be shitting me.

34:18.791 --> 34:21.041
[foreboding music]

34:27.875 --> 34:29.500
[Chike] You worked for Daraja.

34:30.750 --> 34:32.250
Why didn't you tell me?

34:38.291 --> 34:40.708
It is enough for you to know
I have my reasons...

34:44.708 --> 34:47.958
and I expect you
to no longer pry into my affairs.

34:49.375 --> 34:50.583
Yes, Madame.

35:03.083 --> 35:05.166
[indistinct chatter]

35:23.416 --> 35:24.416
Mommy.

35:25.166 --> 35:27.166
You kept me waiting for over an hour.

35:27.625 --> 35:28.958
And you waited...

35:29.500 --> 35:31.000
then it's important.

35:40.833 --> 35:42.750
I wanna talk about Uncle Edem.

35:44.791 --> 35:45.791
Motunrayo.

35:46.041 --> 35:48.291
He feels really bad about what he did.

35:50.500 --> 35:51.708
You spoke with him.

35:52.791 --> 35:54.041
[Mrs. Elesho] Again.

35:55.041 --> 35:56.333
After the memorial?

35:57.708 --> 35:59.208
What is wrong with you?

36:00.000 --> 36:01.958
Uh-uh, Mommy, what?

36:02.500 --> 36:03.541
What?

36:04.416 --> 36:07.875
Even you said that he helped you
and daddy set up Daraja,

36:08.666 --> 36:11.416
and you cut him off
just because of one mistake.

36:11.500 --> 36:12.375
One.

36:12.958 --> 36:15.333
You call what he did one mistake?

36:16.791 --> 36:19.875
Looks like I'm not the only one
you never forgave.

36:20.791 --> 36:22.791
[gloomy music]

36:24.291 --> 36:25.291
Hmm.

36:26.250 --> 36:28.875
Trust you to turn it back to yourself.

36:29.833 --> 36:31.416
It's to be expected.

36:32.625 --> 36:36.166
It's not like you would ever
put the family first.

36:36.250 --> 36:37.375
Uncle Edem is family.

36:37.458 --> 36:39.250
Edem is not part of my family!

36:40.125 --> 36:43.625
Why are you always
so irresponsible, Motunrayo?

36:51.625 --> 36:52.833
[Mrs. Elesho] Motunrayo.

36:59.125 --> 37:01.458
[gloomy music]

37:02.875 --> 37:04.916
-[knocking on door]
-[Motunrayo] <i>Coming.</i>

37:07.250 --> 37:08.750
Why didn't you use your key?

37:08.833 --> 37:10.791
Uh, you told me not to.

37:10.875 --> 37:12.541
[chuckles]
Remember?

37:13.166 --> 37:14.500
Mom said I should check on you.

37:14.833 --> 37:16.208
No, she didn't.

37:17.625 --> 37:20.541
Well, she said you came to see her
and you left upset

37:21.000 --> 37:23.375
and your mommy,
that's pretty much an order.

37:24.708 --> 37:26.083
-[laughs]
-Whatever.

37:28.000 --> 37:30.250
Why would I want to meet him,
somebody that betrayed our family?

37:30.333 --> 37:31.208
Why?

37:31.291 --> 37:33.125
He was our favorite uncle
while we were growing up.

37:33.208 --> 37:34.458
Yeah, that was then.

37:36.083 --> 37:38.458
You have to let bygones be bygones.

37:39.625 --> 37:41.833
[laughs]
You have to let...

37:41.916 --> 37:43.208
Have you met your mother?

37:43.291 --> 37:47.291
[laughs]
Let bygones be bygones indeed.

37:49.500 --> 37:51.958
As a matter of fact,
I'm meeting him tonight.

37:52.083 --> 37:54.500
So, are you coming?

38:01.208 --> 38:02.416
[Motunrayo] Coming?

38:04.000 --> 38:05.125
This is a mistake.

38:05.208 --> 38:06.291
<i>♪ Oya, give them, give them ♪</i>

38:06.375 --> 38:07.875
<i>♪ Left and right, hot-hot ♪</i>

38:07.958 --> 38:10.625
["Miracle" by Dice Ailes playing]

38:10.708 --> 38:14.458
[background chatter]

38:18.333 --> 38:20.708
Janet, your friend is here.

38:31.666 --> 38:34.458
<i>♪ Ah, come bless me
I need a miracle ♪</i>

38:34.541 --> 38:35.916
We have to talk.

38:36.000 --> 38:37.458
[Chike] Okay, I need to change.

38:38.083 --> 38:40.041
If your... If your brother
had picked you up from there,

38:40.125 --> 38:41.958
surely he knows his way back
to the location.

38:42.041 --> 38:43.666
Exactly what I told her.

38:43.750 --> 38:45.166
[Motunrayo] Can you help us?

38:45.541 --> 38:46.666
Please.

38:49.291 --> 38:50.291
Fine.

38:51.708 --> 38:53.500
-Fine.
-Okay.

38:53.583 --> 38:55.291
All right, let me just quickly use
the bathroom,

38:55.375 --> 38:56.583
and then when I'm back, we'll go.

38:56.666 --> 38:57.625
-All right?
-Okay.

39:00.083 --> 39:01.125
[Chike clears throat]

39:07.666 --> 39:08.708
[clears throat]

39:09.666 --> 39:10.708
Um...

39:13.291 --> 39:14.291
Um... I'm...

39:15.208 --> 39:18.583
I'm really sorry. I was...
I was an asshole the first time we met.

39:19.375 --> 39:20.375
Uh-huh.

39:20.458 --> 39:22.583
I thought you were one
of Motunrayo's friends, that's why.

39:22.666 --> 39:23.500
[laughs]

39:23.583 --> 39:24.708
I just...
[chuckles]

39:24.791 --> 39:27.208
Wow, does your sister know you have
such high opinions of her friends?

39:27.291 --> 39:28.791
[laughs]

39:29.291 --> 39:32.125
Trust me, every chance I get, I tell her.

39:32.458 --> 39:33.583
[chuckles]

39:36.041 --> 39:37.125
[clears throat]

39:39.875 --> 39:40.958
Bamidele.

39:41.958 --> 39:45.208
My name is... Janet.

39:48.875 --> 39:49.708
Nice to...

39:49.791 --> 39:51.375
-Sorry, sorry.
-[laughs]

39:51.458 --> 39:53.666
Nice to meet you... Janet.

39:53.750 --> 39:55.208
Nice to meet you too.

39:55.291 --> 39:56.416
[chuckles]

39:56.500 --> 39:57.750
Again, I'm, I'm really sorry...

39:57.833 --> 39:59.166
It's okay, it's okay.

39:59.250 --> 40:00.666
What took you so long?

40:00.750 --> 40:01.750
Number two?

40:01.833 --> 40:02.958
[laughs]

40:03.041 --> 40:04.250
-Sorry, I was...
-Let's go.

40:12.000 --> 40:15.625
It's interesting that a banker
was this close to your family.

40:16.500 --> 40:17.958
That's what you were right,

40:18.416 --> 40:19.541
their banker?

40:20.916 --> 40:22.666
[Edem] Well, I started off as a banker,

40:22.750 --> 40:24.291
and then Tunde took me in as a son.

40:24.375 --> 40:25.666
[Chike] And then you betrayed him.

40:25.750 --> 40:26.833
I was trying to save him.

40:26.916 --> 40:29.208
-Well, he felt differently. Why was that?
-[Bamidele] Uh...

40:29.541 --> 40:30.791
Uncle Edem here.

40:31.125 --> 40:34.000
Listen. You know, when you are young...

40:35.583 --> 40:36.791
you're naive,

40:37.958 --> 40:39.583
you think you have all the answers.

40:40.125 --> 40:42.208
But you know, life deals you a bad hand

40:42.291 --> 40:45.250
and then you lose something as precious
as your entire family.

40:46.833 --> 40:47.916
[Edem] I regret it.

40:48.375 --> 40:51.416
And I sincerely hope you never have
to face the same fate.

40:51.916 --> 40:52.791
[Chike] Hmm.

40:53.958 --> 40:55.291
I know a girl...

40:56.708 --> 40:58.333
the only girl in her family.

40:58.416 --> 41:01.208
Her parents tried to convince her
to go to Italy.

41:02.041 --> 41:03.291
Sometimes...

41:03.875 --> 41:05.541
it's better to lose your family.

41:06.583 --> 41:08.333
What's wrong with going to Italy?

41:08.833 --> 41:10.916
[laughs]

41:11.000 --> 41:12.541
[Motunrayo] Please forgive my brother.

41:12.625 --> 41:15.708
-He has lived a very sheltered life.
-No, no, no. I just...

41:16.125 --> 41:19.125
They wanted her to go to Italy
to become a prostitute.

41:19.208 --> 41:20.708
-Oh.
-So she could send money home.

41:20.791 --> 41:22.125
Oh, oh, oh.

41:22.208 --> 41:23.416
-[chuckles]
-Sorry.

41:23.500 --> 41:27.625
Listen, I think we're getting intense,
let us all calm down a little.

41:27.916 --> 41:29.208
[Edem] I have to be in the kitchen.

41:29.291 --> 41:30.291
I have things to do.

41:30.416 --> 41:31.833
Janet, kitchen now.

41:39.125 --> 41:40.125
What are you playing at?

41:40.208 --> 41:41.916
What am I playing at?
What are you playing at?

41:42.000 --> 41:43.958
It's obvious you're not trying
to get her to marry you.

41:44.416 --> 41:46.666
-[Edem] This is my plan. Stick to it.
-[Chike] Your plan?

41:46.750 --> 41:47.958
I thought it was my plan.

41:51.000 --> 41:52.500
You think this is a joke?

41:53.666 --> 41:55.916
Really? You want to do this right now?

41:57.666 --> 41:58.666
[thumps]

42:01.083 --> 42:02.125
[mutters]

42:06.500 --> 42:07.833
One sec.

42:11.708 --> 42:13.375
I will not say it again.

42:21.791 --> 42:24.333
We need to talk. Now.

42:25.791 --> 42:28.083
[keyboard clacking]

42:30.666 --> 42:32.125
Took you long enough.

42:32.208 --> 42:33.833
[Grace] I told you I was busy.

42:36.791 --> 42:39.166
Edem is not being straightforward with us.

42:39.500 --> 42:41.250
We need to find out what's going on.

42:41.333 --> 42:42.791
[Grace] Who cares what's going on?

42:43.666 --> 42:44.625
[sighs]

42:45.000 --> 42:48.083
He's just a broke playboy
who wants to stay on the gravy train.

42:48.791 --> 42:52.583
Besides, I'm really confused
as to why you're concerned with that.

42:52.666 --> 42:55.958
Rather than being concerned with
actual children who are being poisoned

42:56.041 --> 42:58.083
-by a pharmaceutical company.
-Jesus!

42:58.166 --> 42:59.666
Why does this bother you so much?

42:59.750 --> 43:01.750
Why does it not bother you at all?

43:02.333 --> 43:03.166
[scoffs]

43:06.458 --> 43:07.458
[mumbles]

43:15.541 --> 43:17.458
That is Tobias Vexler.

43:17.541 --> 43:18.666
He's VP Africa.

43:18.750 --> 43:20.541
He's the one that hired us, scroll.

43:23.208 --> 43:25.750
Now, that is Vanessa Strowman.

43:26.083 --> 43:27.708
She's head of compliance.

43:28.291 --> 43:32.375
She received an e-mail yesterday,
with the video of the blackmail.

43:33.291 --> 43:36.458
I expect Tobias is heading back to HQ
to face the music.

43:38.791 --> 43:40.166
I thought you didn't care.

43:40.250 --> 43:42.125
I don't, but you do.

43:42.208 --> 43:43.625
You are my best friend, so...

43:45.291 --> 43:46.291
[Grace] Chike.

43:46.750 --> 43:47.666
Chike.

43:48.750 --> 43:49.958
In my research,

43:50.250 --> 43:54.166
I found out that the Elesho's once had
a three-year-old daughter who had died.

43:54.250 --> 43:55.458
I didn't think anything of it

43:55.541 --> 43:58.750
until one of my clients and contacts
sent me this picture.

43:59.708 --> 44:02.291
[Grace] Her eyes are green
just like Madame's.

44:04.708 --> 44:07.166
She is your child.

44:08.083 --> 44:10.083
[foreboding music]

44:17.166 --> 44:18.458
They took your child?

44:25.416 --> 44:26.833
Is she Mr. Elesho's?

44:32.458 --> 44:35.833
I thought I told you
not to get involved in my affairs.

44:36.416 --> 44:37.875
You involved me.

44:48.458 --> 44:50.666
[gloomy music]

44:53.958 --> 44:55.125
Nurse!

44:56.416 --> 44:57.583
Nur...

45:01.166 --> 45:03.541
No... Ow...

45:03.958 --> 45:05.583
No.
[groans]

45:06.083 --> 45:08.375
Oh, no, no, no.

45:08.458 --> 45:10.375
[Madame pants]

45:10.458 --> 45:11.958
Please, please.

45:12.791 --> 45:14.083
I told you.

45:14.833 --> 45:16.833
He belongs to me.

45:18.625 --> 45:19.625
Him.

45:19.833 --> 45:21.916
And everything he creates.

45:23.541 --> 45:26.541
Including that child
you tried to steal from his body.

45:26.625 --> 45:30.166
Please, where is my baby? Please.

45:31.875 --> 45:35.250
Run away and hide.

45:35.833 --> 45:37.458
[Madame sobbing]

45:37.541 --> 45:41.333
Even fly as far as you can go.

45:41.416 --> 45:42.708
[Madame] Please.

45:43.208 --> 45:46.375
Because if I ever see you again...

45:48.708 --> 45:50.083
I will kill you.

45:50.875 --> 45:54.041
[whimpering]

45:55.583 --> 45:57.208
No, no, please, please.

45:57.291 --> 45:59.583
Ah! Uh, please. Wait, wait, wait.

45:59.666 --> 46:01.916
[groans, sobs]

46:02.791 --> 46:05.333
[Madame] Please wait, wait, wait!

46:05.416 --> 46:06.958
-[Madame groans]
-[clatters]

46:07.041 --> 46:09.375
[Madame] Ah, please wait!

46:09.458 --> 46:11.375
Wait, wait! My baby!
[sobbing]

46:13.041 --> 46:15.000
[screaming]

46:17.041 --> 46:18.875
They took my baby and killed her.

46:18.958 --> 46:20.041
[Chike sighs]

46:21.958 --> 46:23.458
Why didn't you tell me?

46:25.666 --> 46:27.125
I needed you not to know.

46:28.541 --> 46:29.833
-Then what--
-[door opens]

46:32.083 --> 46:34.250
[approaching footsteps]

46:35.791 --> 46:36.708
Kelly?

46:36.791 --> 46:38.208
My name is Dier Spencer.

46:38.291 --> 46:40.958
And I'm an agent with the US
Federal Investigation Division.

46:44.000 --> 46:45.333
You finally sold us out.

46:45.875 --> 46:47.750
[Madame] The NDLEA couldn't meet my price,

46:47.833 --> 46:49.708
but the American government could.

46:49.791 --> 46:52.958
You mentioned you had some information
about some persons of interest

46:53.041 --> 46:54.458
that went missing today.

46:54.958 --> 46:56.416
[Madame] Two drug mules.

46:58.125 --> 46:59.541
Do you know where they are?

47:00.458 --> 47:01.666
[Madame] I might.

47:02.000 --> 47:04.166
I planned to turn you in
almost immediately,

47:04.250 --> 47:07.583
but you proved to be very useful
so I kept postponing.

47:07.875 --> 47:09.583
-Lucky us.
-[Madame] Mm.

47:09.916 --> 47:10.875
Grace!

47:12.583 --> 47:14.875
Grace, Grace, run, run! It's a trap.

47:15.833 --> 47:18.333
-It's a trap.
-Grace doesn't need to run.

47:19.041 --> 47:19.875
Grace.

47:19.958 --> 47:20.833
Yes, Madame.

47:20.916 --> 47:23.833
Hand the original surveillance footage
to Agent Spencer.

47:26.708 --> 47:28.000
You bitch.

47:28.583 --> 47:30.125
They were going to send
my mother to prison

47:30.208 --> 47:31.583
because of the money I sent to her.

47:31.666 --> 47:33.541
My fault, but I couldn't let that happen.

47:33.625 --> 47:35.166
You chose your mother over me?

47:38.875 --> 47:39.958
-[grunting]
-[Grace groaning]

47:43.458 --> 47:46.416
[Chike grunting]

47:50.125 --> 47:51.125
[thwacks]

47:55.375 --> 47:56.458
[handcuffs click]

48:00.541 --> 48:01.500
[spits]

48:03.083 --> 48:04.916
So what was the price you paid for me?

48:05.875 --> 48:06.875
Hmm?

48:07.625 --> 48:09.166
Hope it was worth it.

48:09.500 --> 48:10.458
[Madame] Grace.

48:14.125 --> 48:15.041
[rips]

48:16.208 --> 48:18.541
[somber music]

48:38.166 --> 48:40.333
[Kelly] I recently arrested this person.

48:40.458 --> 48:41.750
Chike Ekeh.

48:41.833 --> 48:44.291
She's a drug dealer and a con-artist,

48:44.541 --> 48:47.125
and your son Bamidele Elesho,

48:47.208 --> 48:49.875
was recently part
of her latest confidence scheme.

48:50.708 --> 48:52.500
This is nonsense. This is nonsense.

48:52.583 --> 48:54.375
We actually have evidence
on both of your meetings.

48:54.458 --> 48:56.333
This is ridiculous, I was at, uh...

48:56.416 --> 48:57.625
the hotel to meet Blue Stream--

48:57.708 --> 48:58.666
Stream Capital.

48:58.750 --> 48:59.625
Yes!

49:00.125 --> 49:03.541
[camera shutter clicking]

49:03.625 --> 49:06.083
We had e-mail exchanges showing that,

49:06.166 --> 49:08.666
Blue Stream Capital
was a front for your meeting.

49:08.750 --> 49:10.916
I, I never sent any e-mail.

49:11.000 --> 49:13.000
And you don't even have proof
that I did this.

49:13.541 --> 49:14.958
[camera shutter clicks]

49:15.541 --> 49:17.583
I'm actually doing this as courtesy.

49:18.000 --> 49:20.083
You are a US citizen,

49:20.166 --> 49:22.416
and you're a personal friend
of the ambassador.

49:22.791 --> 49:24.750
We will be charging Miss Ekeh next week,

49:24.833 --> 49:27.041
and the information
on your son will be out.

49:27.666 --> 49:30.541
But, my son says he is innocent.

49:30.625 --> 49:31.583
Yeah.

49:31.666 --> 49:35.416
Miss Ekeh was part of an international
drug smuggling ring.

49:35.958 --> 49:39.375
It is more likely that any
of her associates will be flagged.

49:39.750 --> 49:40.791
I see.

49:43.791 --> 49:45.833
Agent Spencer, thank you.

49:46.458 --> 49:48.083
Regards to the ambassador.

49:56.083 --> 49:57.125
-Bamidele.
-Mom.

49:57.208 --> 49:59.500
[stutters]
I didn't...

49:59.583 --> 50:00.916
I didn't do that, Mom.

50:01.000 --> 50:02.250
I swear, I didn't.

50:02.333 --> 50:03.666
I only met that woman once!

50:04.166 --> 50:06.916
When she took us
to, to Uncle Edem's house, right?

50:07.500 --> 50:08.583
Tell her!

50:09.333 --> 50:10.875
What am I supposed to say?

50:11.208 --> 50:14.166
I met a random woman
who turned out to be Uncle Edem's tenant.

50:14.250 --> 50:16.291
How am I supposed to know
when you met her?

50:16.375 --> 50:18.041
She was working with Edem.

50:18.125 --> 50:19.791
You were working with Edem.

50:19.875 --> 50:21.333
-Mom... Mom...
-Bamidele, how could you?

50:21.416 --> 50:23.125
Mom, I'll never do such.

50:23.208 --> 50:26.375
I will never do anything like that, Mom,
I swear to you, I will never... Oh...

50:26.458 --> 50:29.291
Son, you will have to give up
your shares in Daraja.

50:30.291 --> 50:31.375
Mom.

50:31.708 --> 50:34.875
Your name has just been linked
with a drug dealer.

50:34.958 --> 50:36.208
What if he's innocent?

50:36.916 --> 50:38.500
No, it doesn't matter.

50:38.583 --> 50:40.125
No one will believe it,

50:40.208 --> 50:42.458
and the entire family will be ruined.

50:42.541 --> 50:43.416
Mom.

50:43.500 --> 50:46.041
Son, you will have to do this
for the family

50:46.125 --> 50:48.083
and you will have to do it now.

50:50.250 --> 50:51.375
Motunrayo.

50:51.666 --> 50:53.208
You will take the shares.

50:53.875 --> 50:54.750
[Motunrayo] What?

50:54.833 --> 50:55.666
Why?

50:55.750 --> 50:57.625
You are the future of the family

50:57.708 --> 50:59.958
and you will have to do this one.

51:00.041 --> 51:01.041
[sighs]

51:01.125 --> 51:03.416
-[groans]
-Mom, I, I, think that...

51:03.625 --> 51:05.166
Mom, Mom.

51:12.333 --> 51:14.416
[gloomy music]

51:29.916 --> 51:32.333
[gloomy music continues]

51:45.750 --> 51:46.916
You were right.

51:47.625 --> 51:49.291
She gave me the shares.

51:51.625 --> 51:53.625
[somber music]

52:05.333 --> 52:09.458
[inaudible dialogue]

52:15.333 --> 52:17.708
[somber music]

52:32.083 --> 52:34.125
-[Tunde] <i>Tell her!</i>
-[Mrs. Elesho] <i>You do not understand...</i>

52:34.208 --> 52:35.625
-[Tunde] <i>You have to tell her!</i>
-<i>Why, why?</i>

52:35.708 --> 52:37.708
-Why do you want to tell her?
-[Tunde] She's her mother!

52:37.791 --> 52:39.500
-No, I am her mother!
-Her mother won't take

52:39.583 --> 52:41.625
this rubbish from you.
Stop this rubbish. C'mon, stop this!

52:41.708 --> 52:43.875
[Mrs. Elesho] I am her mother,
you were supposed to be with me

52:43.958 --> 52:46.416
instead of running off
with that bloody slut!

52:46.500 --> 52:47.833
[Tunde] Rubbish.

52:47.916 --> 52:50.166
Daddy! Daddy!
[sobs]

52:51.375 --> 52:53.041
-[whimpers]
-What are you doing here?

52:53.125 --> 52:54.583
[sobbing]

52:54.666 --> 52:57.333
-[screaming]
-Get into your room!

52:57.416 --> 53:00.791
[in Yoruba]
Useless child, disgraceful child!

53:00.875 --> 53:02.625
-Get into your room
-[wailing]

53:04.333 --> 53:06.125
[Mrs. Elesho in English]
Crying like a banshee.

53:06.708 --> 53:08.666
[whimpering]

53:10.708 --> 53:13.833
[sobbing]

53:16.125 --> 53:18.208
[somber music]

53:26.458 --> 53:28.541
[sobbing]

53:50.166 --> 53:52.291
[ominous music]

54:01.416 --> 54:03.500
[music box playing]

54:16.916 --> 54:18.958
[somber music]

54:31.583 --> 54:33.500
[sniffles, pants]

54:46.833 --> 54:50.875
[sobbing]

54:54.083 --> 54:55.791
Motunrayo, what are you doing here?

54:57.666 --> 54:59.041
[sniffles]
Uh...

54:59.375 --> 55:01.500
I'm so sorry, Aunty.

55:03.125 --> 55:04.666
I killed her.

55:05.625 --> 55:09.125
I'm so, so sorry.

55:09.500 --> 55:12.625
[sobbing]

55:19.291 --> 55:21.958
[both whimpering]

55:23.666 --> 55:26.333
She has refused to leave
since she got here.

55:32.916 --> 55:34.833
[Edem] Motunrayo, my dear.

55:38.500 --> 55:40.625
Your people are frantic with worry.

55:42.333 --> 55:43.750
You have to go home.

55:44.458 --> 55:45.583
Please.

55:48.541 --> 55:51.916
Uncle Edem, I killed her.

55:53.041 --> 55:54.708
I killed Charity.

55:55.083 --> 55:56.291
No, you didn't.

55:58.375 --> 55:59.750
[Motunrayo] I was watching her.

56:01.958 --> 56:05.833
I took my eyes off for a second...

56:08.666 --> 56:11.041
and she jumped off the balcony.

56:12.291 --> 56:13.708
It was just...

56:14.625 --> 56:16.458
for a second, I swear.

56:21.291 --> 56:22.958
[Edem] It's not your fault.

56:24.041 --> 56:25.333
Are you hearing me?

56:26.583 --> 56:28.000
It was an accident.

56:28.458 --> 56:29.958
It can happen to anyone.

56:31.500 --> 56:33.000
I need you to go home.

56:33.875 --> 56:35.958
So, your people can take care of you.

56:38.041 --> 56:40.875
I owe you, Aunty Enitan.

56:41.541 --> 56:43.333
More than I can ever repay.

56:45.333 --> 56:49.166
If there is anything you need from me...

56:51.958 --> 56:54.458
it's yours without question.

56:57.750 --> 56:59.208
I'm so sorry.

57:06.958 --> 57:09.041
[somber music]

57:17.041 --> 57:18.166
Miss Motunrayo.

57:19.291 --> 57:21.208
Will you be kind to walk me out?

57:25.833 --> 57:27.125
Of course.

57:36.500 --> 57:39.000
[somber music]

57:51.000 --> 57:53.083
[upbeat music]

57:57.791 --> 57:59.083
Hey!

58:02.041 --> 58:04.541
-Look at you.
-[laughs]

58:07.166 --> 58:08.916
[Madame] It's been so long.

58:15.583 --> 58:16.791
I called the number,

58:16.875 --> 58:19.083
all it gave me was an address
and then, it hung up.

58:19.166 --> 58:21.750
Oh, that's how we keep The Academy safe.

58:22.375 --> 58:23.583
What is this place?

58:23.666 --> 58:24.666
Is it, uh...

58:25.083 --> 58:26.333
-Whor--
-Whorehouse?

58:26.458 --> 58:28.708
[both laugh]

58:31.166 --> 58:32.583
It's a private club.

58:33.291 --> 58:37.125
Well, I entertain for your father
long enough to understand that,

58:37.208 --> 58:39.875
powerful men want a place
where they can be themselves...

58:40.833 --> 58:44.000
away from the world,
and The Academy provides that.

58:44.083 --> 58:46.666
Well, it kind of sounds like a whorehouse.

58:46.750 --> 58:48.416
[laughs]

58:48.500 --> 58:51.916
Well, men just want to be listened to.

58:52.000 --> 58:55.083
You'll be amazed at the secrets
they spill here.

58:55.666 --> 59:00.208
For example, it was here
that I learned your father had passed on.

59:01.166 --> 59:03.833
In spite of everything, I'm sorry.

59:05.416 --> 59:07.708
I loved him once upon a time.

59:07.916 --> 59:09.625
He was married to my mother.

59:09.875 --> 59:13.250
So you understand why he fell for me.

59:13.333 --> 59:16.958
[both laugh]

59:18.500 --> 59:20.583
I was so glad you could come,
I didn't think you would.

59:20.666 --> 59:23.541
I gave you my word.
Anything you want, it's yours.

59:24.083 --> 59:25.583
Hmm.
[clicks tongue]

59:27.333 --> 59:30.166
A friend told me
that your father left the bank

59:30.250 --> 59:31.916
to you and your brother?

59:34.791 --> 59:36.750
Your father had three children.

59:38.250 --> 59:40.125
It should have been divided equally.

59:42.333 --> 59:44.041
Charity is dead, Aunty Enitan.

59:44.125 --> 59:47.333
And I am her only living relative.

59:47.750 --> 59:49.708
I should be her beneficiary

59:51.958 --> 59:53.208
[sighs]

59:53.791 --> 59:55.416
I'd give you my shares in a second,

59:55.500 --> 59:59.041
-but my mom has the highest shares.
-I know the structure.

59:59.125 --> 1:00:01.625
And I can't sell without her permission.

1:00:01.708 --> 1:00:03.250
[Madame] I know the structure.

1:00:03.833 --> 1:00:05.958
What I'm saying to you is this.

1:00:06.875 --> 1:00:07.958
One day,

1:00:09.000 --> 1:00:13.083
I will come to you
to help me get goals shares,

1:00:13.166 --> 1:00:14.791
and you will do so.

1:00:18.166 --> 1:00:19.541
Is that fair?

1:00:21.916 --> 1:00:24.041
[gloomy music]

1:00:29.000 --> 1:00:30.541
[snoring]

1:00:31.083 --> 1:00:32.625
[knocking on door]

1:00:33.125 --> 1:00:34.125
[snorts]

1:00:36.291 --> 1:00:38.666
-[snores]
-[knocking on door]

1:00:38.750 --> 1:00:39.833
[coughs]

1:00:40.083 --> 1:00:41.250
[snoring]

1:00:43.666 --> 1:00:45.500
[knocking on door]

1:00:45.708 --> 1:00:46.708
[clicks tongue]

1:00:46.916 --> 1:00:48.041
[snorts]

1:00:49.416 --> 1:00:50.458
[sucks teeth]

1:00:51.166 --> 1:00:55.458
-[sighs]
-[knocking on door]

1:01:00.416 --> 1:01:02.083
Yes, hello, can I help you?

1:01:02.166 --> 1:01:03.500
[deliveryman] Yeah. This is for you.

1:01:06.541 --> 1:01:08.083
Okay. Thank you.

1:01:23.916 --> 1:01:26.041
[gloomy music]

1:01:32.125 --> 1:01:34.458
[Motunrayo]
<i>You want me to set up my brother.</i>

1:01:35.125 --> 1:01:36.708
Only for a short time.

1:01:37.208 --> 1:01:40.416
As long as this project takes to,
you know it's just a short time.

1:01:40.500 --> 1:01:41.458
No.

1:01:41.541 --> 1:01:43.458
I can't do it, I won't do it.

1:01:44.333 --> 1:01:47.125
"I owe you more than I can ever repay you.

1:01:47.750 --> 1:01:51.208
If you ever need anything from me,
it is yours without question."

1:01:51.291 --> 1:01:53.000
Your words, not mine.

1:01:55.416 --> 1:01:56.541
[sighs]

1:02:00.458 --> 1:02:01.875
What do you need me to do?

1:02:02.541 --> 1:02:04.083
[knocking on door]

1:02:04.166 --> 1:02:06.375
-[door creaks]
-[Motunrayo groans]

1:02:07.083 --> 1:02:08.375
[Motunrayo] Can I help you?

1:02:11.541 --> 1:02:13.833
Uh, are you crazy?

1:02:15.166 --> 1:02:17.208
My name is Grace, I work with Madame.

1:02:26.833 --> 1:02:27.875
What do you want?

1:02:27.958 --> 1:02:29.208
To prepare you.

1:02:30.375 --> 1:02:31.958
Prepare me for what?

1:02:33.083 --> 1:02:36.541
To convince Chike that you're the target
of a love triangle operation

1:02:36.625 --> 1:02:38.041
with Mr. Edem Bucknur.

1:02:38.125 --> 1:02:40.000
[snickers, sighs]

1:02:40.708 --> 1:02:42.416
Uncle Edem and I?

1:02:42.916 --> 1:02:46.291
That is so absurd,
no one is going to believe that.

1:02:46.833 --> 1:02:48.791
Chike is Madame's most skilled operative

1:02:48.875 --> 1:02:51.666
and if you do not prepare well,
everything is going to fall apart.

1:02:56.666 --> 1:02:58.125
How long do I have?

1:02:58.208 --> 1:02:59.291
[Grace] <i>One month.</i>

1:03:00.041 --> 1:03:01.291
What are you doing here?

1:03:05.250 --> 1:03:06.375
[sighs]

1:03:07.750 --> 1:03:09.583
It is good to see you too, Toyin.

1:03:10.250 --> 1:03:14.000
What are you doing here?

1:03:15.875 --> 1:03:17.708
I came to pay my respects.

1:03:20.250 --> 1:03:21.791
You are not welcome here.

1:03:23.208 --> 1:03:24.333
Leave.

1:03:26.083 --> 1:03:28.500
Toyin, it doesn't always have to...

1:03:29.250 --> 1:03:31.208
Would you rather I call security?

1:03:35.666 --> 1:03:37.875
[tense music]

1:03:46.583 --> 1:03:48.708
What is wrong with you?

1:03:49.166 --> 1:03:50.583
What did I do?

1:03:50.875 --> 1:03:52.416
He came up to me.

1:03:52.708 --> 1:03:53.833
What was I supposed to do?

1:03:53.916 --> 1:03:55.208
Turn and walk away?

1:03:55.541 --> 1:03:56.500
Yes.

1:03:57.500 --> 1:03:58.583
Mom?

1:03:59.166 --> 1:04:00.208
[sighs]

1:04:11.041 --> 1:04:12.708
[Motunrayo] <i>Can I ask you a question?</i>

1:04:13.875 --> 1:04:17.708
Your face changes
whenever Chike's name comes up.

1:04:18.125 --> 1:04:19.375
What's up with that?

1:04:19.625 --> 1:04:20.541
Mm.

1:04:20.958 --> 1:04:23.416
You are getting really good at this.

1:04:23.500 --> 1:04:25.416
I have a good teacher. Mm?

1:04:25.500 --> 1:04:26.958
[chuckles]

1:04:27.708 --> 1:04:29.125
Don't drink too much.

1:04:29.208 --> 1:04:30.708
Tomorrow is a very big day.

1:04:33.041 --> 1:04:34.833
[Motunrayo] <i>I've ordered the drinks.</i>

1:04:35.541 --> 1:04:38.125
<i>Oh, god, I'm so nervous.</i>

1:04:38.208 --> 1:04:40.416
I never thought I'll be this nervous.

1:04:41.000 --> 1:04:44.500
You're going to be fine.
Remember, just play yourself.

1:04:44.666 --> 1:04:46.458
I would never do this.

1:04:46.833 --> 1:04:48.958
Oh, yes, but she doesn't know that.

1:04:49.583 --> 1:04:50.666
Have fun.

1:04:51.541 --> 1:04:53.083
[sighs deeply]
Okay.

1:04:53.166 --> 1:04:55.208
[pants]

1:04:55.291 --> 1:04:57.500
Have fun.
[sighs sharply]

1:05:02.541 --> 1:05:05.041
[tense music]

1:05:08.833 --> 1:05:10.500
[Chike] Good evening, ma.

1:05:10.583 --> 1:05:11.791
Should I open it?

1:05:12.208 --> 1:05:13.375
Sure, open it.

1:05:16.875 --> 1:05:19.166
[foreboding music]

1:05:21.875 --> 1:05:23.958
-Do you know who you are talking about?
-I don't care.

1:05:24.041 --> 1:05:25.291
Excuse me.

1:05:25.375 --> 1:05:27.208
Officer, what seems to be the problem?

1:05:27.291 --> 1:05:28.916
What's the fuck is wrong with my phone?

1:05:29.000 --> 1:05:33.416
[indistinct chatter]

1:05:38.958 --> 1:05:40.083
[Chike] Are you okay?

1:05:43.541 --> 1:05:44.791
[Motunrayo] You.

1:05:45.541 --> 1:05:46.916
[Motunrayo laughs]

1:05:47.666 --> 1:05:49.541
Can I borrow your phone?

1:05:54.833 --> 1:05:56.416
[Chike] <i>Oh, I can't believe
that this guy...</i>

1:05:56.500 --> 1:05:58.541
-[dog barking]
-...locked my house.

1:05:58.791 --> 1:06:00.458
I can't believe
that this guy locked my house.

1:06:00.541 --> 1:06:02.333
God help me punish Mr. Edem.

1:06:02.416 --> 1:06:03.708
God will punish him.

1:06:06.750 --> 1:06:07.916
[Chike] Do you know them?

1:06:09.666 --> 1:06:13.583
That's my dad, Edem, and Aunt Enitan.

1:06:13.666 --> 1:06:15.041
My dad's former PA.

1:06:15.125 --> 1:06:18.708
[coughing]

1:06:19.791 --> 1:06:21.916
[foreboding music]

1:06:28.958 --> 1:06:30.500
-[Chike] Uh-uh.
-Okay, so.

1:06:30.583 --> 1:06:32.208
[Chike] No, but we had a deal, no, like,

1:06:32.291 --> 1:06:34.333
you pay my rent and I take you home.

1:06:34.750 --> 1:06:36.583
But my car is already here.

1:06:36.666 --> 1:06:37.750
[chuckles]

1:06:38.833 --> 1:06:40.000
[relieved sigh]

1:06:44.875 --> 1:06:46.416
[Motunrayo] <i>Thanks for the ride.</i>

1:06:47.083 --> 1:06:48.333
<i>No wahala.</i>

1:06:49.875 --> 1:06:50.833
[sighs]

1:06:51.375 --> 1:06:52.791
You know I love you, right?

1:06:54.041 --> 1:06:56.291
I love how you're always there for me.

1:06:59.250 --> 1:07:00.333
[sighs]

1:07:01.125 --> 1:07:03.125
I will... see you around.

1:07:03.500 --> 1:07:04.833
Take care of yourself, huh?

1:07:04.916 --> 1:07:06.000
I will.

1:07:07.500 --> 1:07:10.416
[car engine revs]

1:07:17.708 --> 1:07:19.958
[foreboding music]

1:07:28.958 --> 1:07:30.416
[knocking on door]

1:07:34.291 --> 1:07:35.583
[knocking continues]

1:07:35.666 --> 1:07:37.458
[Motunrayo] Hold on a second.

1:07:43.125 --> 1:07:44.291
What's wrong?

1:07:44.375 --> 1:07:45.916
[Grace] We didn't get what we needed.

1:07:46.416 --> 1:07:47.791
What do you mean?

1:07:47.875 --> 1:07:51.291
We couldn't get an isolated picture of him
and her alone by the car.

1:07:51.375 --> 1:07:52.541
Damn it.

1:07:53.375 --> 1:07:54.500
[sighs]

1:07:55.583 --> 1:07:58.208
Wait a minute, why are you here?

1:07:58.291 --> 1:07:59.750
[Grace] We would need to try again.

1:08:00.666 --> 1:08:01.625
What?

1:08:01.708 --> 1:08:02.791
How?

1:08:02.875 --> 1:08:04.791
I want to talk about Uncle Edem.

1:08:05.916 --> 1:08:08.458
I'm meeting him tonight, so...

1:08:09.041 --> 1:08:10.208
are you coming?

1:08:11.750 --> 1:08:13.458
All right, let me just quickly
use the bathroom,

1:08:13.541 --> 1:08:14.833
and then when I'm back, we'll go.

1:08:14.916 --> 1:08:15.916
-All right?
-Okay.

1:08:17.916 --> 1:08:19.500
Hey, what's going on?

1:08:22.041 --> 1:08:23.916
[Grace] <i>We're getting the picture.
Hold on.</i>

1:08:26.833 --> 1:08:29.166
<i>That's it. You can come out now.</i>

1:08:33.666 --> 1:08:35.166
<i>Did you hear me? We are on again.</i>

1:08:35.250 --> 1:08:37.125
Yes, yes, I heard you.

1:08:37.583 --> 1:08:38.750
I heard you.

1:08:44.416 --> 1:08:46.125
[sobs]

1:08:46.708 --> 1:08:47.791
[sighs sharply]

1:09:01.791 --> 1:09:03.916
[Kelly] Thank you for meeting me
on such short notice.

1:09:08.333 --> 1:09:10.875
[gloomy music]

1:09:25.791 --> 1:09:27.041
You were right.

1:09:27.875 --> 1:09:29.541
She gave me the shares.

1:09:29.625 --> 1:09:32.291
So I'll see you tonight?

1:09:36.250 --> 1:09:37.625
[sighs]

1:09:41.625 --> 1:09:43.083
[door squeaks]

1:09:43.166 --> 1:09:45.750
Mommy, you need to come with me, now.

1:09:46.500 --> 1:09:47.833
Come with you where?

1:09:50.458 --> 1:09:52.708
Motunrayo, what are you talking about?

1:09:54.041 --> 1:09:55.541
It's past ten.

1:09:56.041 --> 1:09:58.375
Mommy, we can save Bamidele.

1:09:58.458 --> 1:09:59.833
[Madame] <i>Welcome, Toyin.</i>

1:10:12.083 --> 1:10:13.291
What do you want?

1:10:13.375 --> 1:10:15.541
Are you sure you don't want to sit?

1:10:16.708 --> 1:10:18.833
Or should I pat you down for weapons?

1:10:19.583 --> 1:10:22.083
After all, you said you will kill me.

1:10:22.166 --> 1:10:23.500
Last time we met.

1:10:23.583 --> 1:10:27.416
Is this supposed to be revenge
for Charity?

1:10:27.500 --> 1:10:29.416
Don't you dare speak her name.

1:10:29.500 --> 1:10:31.166
The name that I gave her.

1:10:32.375 --> 1:10:34.375
She called me Mommy.

1:10:34.958 --> 1:10:39.125
And she jumped up for joy
anytime I entered the room.

1:10:39.208 --> 1:10:41.750
She is dead because of you.

1:10:41.833 --> 1:10:44.416
Oh, and that is how you justify...

1:10:45.041 --> 1:10:46.541
whatever this is.

1:10:52.875 --> 1:10:54.541
Is that what she told you?

1:10:55.250 --> 1:10:57.666
That you have to make amends for Charity.

1:11:01.500 --> 1:11:03.750
Darling, it was an accident.

1:11:10.458 --> 1:11:11.458
Wow.

1:11:13.708 --> 1:11:17.416
That's the first time
you've ever said those words to me.

1:11:18.208 --> 1:11:20.208
[Madame] Agent Spencer is a friend.

1:11:22.625 --> 1:11:26.791
I may be able to convince her
to charge Chike Ekeh

1:11:27.541 --> 1:11:29.708
for her other crimes...

1:11:30.791 --> 1:11:33.041
and leave out the recent escapades.

1:11:33.125 --> 1:11:35.166
Motunrayo, you agreed to this...

1:11:36.250 --> 1:11:39.416
to have your brother labeled
a drug dealer?

1:11:39.500 --> 1:11:41.250
He doesn't have to be.

1:11:42.291 --> 1:11:46.500
All we have to do
is hand over 33 percent of Daraja

1:11:46.916 --> 1:11:49.541
which is what Charity
would have inherited anyway.

1:11:53.000 --> 1:11:54.458
Is that true, Enitan?

1:11:57.208 --> 1:12:01.583
Will 33 percent make the charges go away?

1:12:01.666 --> 1:12:05.083
[laughing]

1:12:08.166 --> 1:12:10.333
I have always loved you...

1:12:12.083 --> 1:12:13.208
Toyin.

1:12:13.750 --> 1:12:18.708
You have always seen the big picture.

1:12:19.125 --> 1:12:20.708
[laughs]

1:12:21.083 --> 1:12:22.125
What?

1:12:23.208 --> 1:12:24.708
What are you talking about?

1:12:24.791 --> 1:12:27.083
You will hand over your golden share.

1:12:27.833 --> 1:12:31.208
And you, 75 percent of Daraja.

1:12:31.958 --> 1:12:32.875
What?

1:12:33.291 --> 1:12:35.666
We had a deal.
You're only supposed to take a third!

1:12:35.750 --> 1:12:36.750
What are you doing?

1:12:36.833 --> 1:12:38.125
Silly girl.

1:12:39.791 --> 1:12:43.166
Did you actually think
that this was an attempt at restitution?

1:12:44.791 --> 1:12:47.083
Mommy, we don't have to agree to this.

1:12:48.000 --> 1:12:49.250
We can fight this.

1:12:49.333 --> 1:12:50.291
Oh.

1:12:51.416 --> 1:12:55.208
And you think that we can leave here
without agreeing to this?

1:12:56.750 --> 1:12:58.916
Actually, I have a number of...

1:12:59.625 --> 1:13:03.416
strapping young men
who will make life very hard for you.

1:13:04.375 --> 1:13:08.583
And I'm sure you wouldn't want me
to resort to that, would you?

1:13:09.541 --> 1:13:10.416
[Madame] Hm?

1:13:10.500 --> 1:13:14.958
[laughing]

1:13:16.541 --> 1:13:19.125
I'm sorry. I, I didn't know.

1:13:25.000 --> 1:13:26.125
We have a deal.

1:13:26.208 --> 1:13:28.750
[gloomy music]

1:13:38.250 --> 1:13:40.666
[gloomy music continues]

1:13:48.416 --> 1:13:49.583
[glasses clink]

1:13:56.958 --> 1:13:58.125
[Motunrayo] Mom?

1:13:58.666 --> 1:14:00.333
Let me explain.

1:14:04.041 --> 1:14:05.250
Motunrayo.

1:14:07.041 --> 1:14:09.250
You destroyed your family.

1:14:10.416 --> 1:14:11.833
For a woman...

1:14:12.916 --> 1:14:14.250
for a whore...

1:14:14.583 --> 1:14:16.750
who tried to destroy my marriage.

1:14:17.375 --> 1:14:19.250
Mommy, it wasn't like that.

1:14:19.833 --> 1:14:22.291
I only wanted
to make it right for Charity.

1:14:22.375 --> 1:14:23.416
Yes.

1:14:23.958 --> 1:14:26.875
And you ended up destroying us.

1:14:28.666 --> 1:14:31.875
It would have been better if you had died

1:14:31.958 --> 1:14:33.583
instead of her.

1:14:35.583 --> 1:14:39.041
Mom, I will do whatever it takes
to make it right.

1:14:39.708 --> 1:14:41.000
[Motunrayo] I promise.

1:14:52.083 --> 1:14:53.250
-[thwacks]
-[yelps]

1:14:54.500 --> 1:14:56.500
[sobs]

1:15:04.041 --> 1:15:06.416
[somber music]

1:15:31.750 --> 1:15:33.250
[knocks on door]

1:15:38.416 --> 1:15:40.791
[water pattering]

1:15:41.791 --> 1:15:43.041
[knocks on door]

1:15:43.875 --> 1:15:45.666
[water pattering]

1:16:00.375 --> 1:16:02.708
[ominous music]

1:16:11.416 --> 1:16:12.375
Hello?

1:16:13.500 --> 1:16:14.625
We have a problem.

1:16:15.500 --> 1:16:17.166
Isn't that always the case?

1:16:20.416 --> 1:16:21.416
Mm-hm.

1:16:28.083 --> 1:16:29.041
Okay.

1:16:32.125 --> 1:16:33.500
[water pattering]

1:16:37.333 --> 1:16:40.750
Whatever, the size, he'll pay.

1:16:40.833 --> 1:16:41.958
-[Chike] Oh.
-[Grace] Yes.

1:16:42.041 --> 1:16:43.791
He is blowing the whistle on Megapharma.

1:16:43.875 --> 1:16:46.708
[Chike] Okay. Good.
Madame wants to see you.

1:16:46.791 --> 1:16:48.041
[Madame] Report.

1:16:50.416 --> 1:16:53.083
I said report.

1:16:53.458 --> 1:16:56.416
Pastor Dimeji is ready
to turn on Megapharma.

1:16:56.500 --> 1:16:58.125
He'll be sending an e-mail tonight.

1:17:00.166 --> 1:17:02.083
I knew you'd be successful.

1:17:02.666 --> 1:17:06.083
That's why I went ahead
to set up a meeting with Megapharma.

1:17:06.166 --> 1:17:07.291
I don't quite understand.

1:17:07.375 --> 1:17:10.125
Oh, you see,
to be a successful rat-catcher,

1:17:10.625 --> 1:17:13.291
you need to breed rats.

1:17:13.791 --> 1:17:14.791
Of course.

1:17:14.875 --> 1:17:17.583
You and Chike need to come up with a plan

1:17:17.666 --> 1:17:19.166
to keep the Pastor quiet,

1:17:19.500 --> 1:17:24.166
whilst I consider how much I'm going to
charge Megapharma for the privilege.

1:17:26.125 --> 1:17:27.375
[Madame] That's not all.

1:17:29.041 --> 1:17:33.125
The first folder contains all you need
to know about Bamidele Elesho.

1:17:34.000 --> 1:17:38.875
We need to establish a relationship
between him and Blue Stream.

1:17:38.958 --> 1:17:43.541
The second folder contains a signed
profile from the US government,

1:17:43.625 --> 1:17:46.375
granting you immunity
for all your drug crimes.

1:17:47.583 --> 1:17:48.791
[stuttering]

1:17:49.083 --> 1:17:50.791
Why are you offering me this?

1:17:50.875 --> 1:17:53.500
Chike will take the fall with Bamidele.

1:17:53.583 --> 1:17:55.416
No, Chike is my sister.

1:17:55.500 --> 1:17:56.541
I will never betray her.

1:17:56.625 --> 1:17:59.833
Never betray her
even if it means saving yourself?

1:17:59.916 --> 1:18:00.833
No!

1:18:01.083 --> 1:18:02.791
What about saving your mother?

1:18:04.750 --> 1:18:06.500
She received the money you sent her.

1:18:07.250 --> 1:18:09.625
[Kelly] Which makes her an accessory
after the fact.

1:18:10.500 --> 1:18:12.208
That's ten years in prison.

1:18:12.708 --> 1:18:14.500
[Madame] Oh, by the way,
this is Agent Spencer.

1:18:14.583 --> 1:18:17.416
She works with the United States
Drugs Agency.

1:18:17.958 --> 1:18:19.875
[Madame] Chike is going down.

1:18:19.958 --> 1:18:21.166
Question is...

1:18:21.500 --> 1:18:23.916
whether you choose to go with her.

1:18:29.041 --> 1:18:31.083
-[Dimeji] I can't get enough of you.
-[Grace screams]

1:18:31.166 --> 1:18:32.750
[Grace] Yes, Daddy.
[laughs]

1:18:32.833 --> 1:18:33.750
[Grace] Wow.

1:18:33.833 --> 1:18:35.666
Thou art in such a hurry.

1:18:35.750 --> 1:18:36.708
[Dimeji] Yes, I am.

1:18:36.791 --> 1:18:38.166
[Grace] Welcome, baby.

1:18:38.250 --> 1:18:39.333
[Dimeji and Grace laugh]

1:18:41.708 --> 1:18:42.875
Hmm...

1:18:43.583 --> 1:18:44.916
[Grace] Ah.

1:18:45.000 --> 1:18:46.375
[Dimeji] So where were we?

1:18:47.458 --> 1:18:48.583
[Dimeji exhales sharply]

1:18:48.666 --> 1:18:49.625
[smooches]

1:18:51.041 --> 1:18:52.041
[Chike] Okay.

1:18:52.666 --> 1:18:53.916
Jesus!

1:18:54.375 --> 1:18:56.041
-I think I've seen enough.
-[Grace chuckles]

1:18:59.458 --> 1:19:01.291
Who are you, and what...
what are you doing in my--

1:19:01.375 --> 1:19:02.541
In your room?

1:19:03.666 --> 1:19:06.333
Well, Pastor Dimeji, I'm your friend.

1:19:07.708 --> 1:19:09.375
[Chike] Isn't that right, Tayo?

1:19:09.458 --> 1:19:10.708
Yes, it is.

1:19:15.625 --> 1:19:17.291
[stutters]
Why are we...

1:19:17.375 --> 1:19:18.375
[sighs]

1:19:18.458 --> 1:19:19.791
Why are we letting this happen?

1:19:20.416 --> 1:19:21.916
Okay, what would you have me do?

1:19:24.375 --> 1:19:26.708
Chike, we can run away, we can go.

1:19:26.791 --> 1:19:28.458
With all Madame knows about us?

1:19:28.750 --> 1:19:31.541
Do you want to spend the rest of your life
running from the NDLEA?

1:19:33.250 --> 1:19:34.875
What about what we know about her?

1:19:35.291 --> 1:19:36.916
We can bring her down.

1:19:39.458 --> 1:19:42.375
Come on, Chike,
is this the life you want to live?

1:19:42.458 --> 1:19:43.708
Grace, I get it.

1:19:43.791 --> 1:19:45.833
You like Pastor Dimeji,
you like these children,

1:19:45.916 --> 1:19:47.791
and what's happening to them is a tragedy.

1:19:47.875 --> 1:19:49.458
But, Grace, this isn't our fight.

1:19:49.541 --> 1:19:51.083
We could make it our fight.

1:19:54.166 --> 1:19:55.416
You called.

1:19:56.041 --> 1:19:58.750
Now, do you have anything on the Enitan
that worked for Daraja?

1:20:01.916 --> 1:20:03.125
Thank you.

1:20:06.625 --> 1:20:08.708
[gloomy music]

1:20:11.541 --> 1:20:12.958
Thank you for coming

1:20:14.000 --> 1:20:15.625
-[Grace] Dimeji--
-What do you want?

1:20:16.208 --> 1:20:17.625
I'm sorry.

1:20:17.708 --> 1:20:20.250
Don't you dare apologize.

1:20:21.833 --> 1:20:23.625
You approached me.

1:20:26.541 --> 1:20:29.666
You convinced me to spill the beans
on Megapharma,

1:20:29.750 --> 1:20:32.375
and then you blackmail me into silence.

1:20:33.250 --> 1:20:35.625
-I'm sorry about everything.
-[Dimeji] No!

1:20:35.708 --> 1:20:37.125
You don't get to do this.

1:20:38.583 --> 1:20:42.041
You don't get to destroy my life,
and then do this.

1:20:42.125 --> 1:20:43.125
No.

1:20:43.625 --> 1:20:44.958
What kind of person are you?

1:20:45.041 --> 1:20:46.666
Somebody who loves you.

1:20:47.083 --> 1:20:50.500
Dimeji, somebody who is here
to find out if there's still ever

1:20:50.583 --> 1:20:52.583
any chance for us, please.

1:21:03.583 --> 1:21:04.875
Go to hell.

1:21:06.375 --> 1:21:08.375
[somber music]

1:21:12.666 --> 1:21:13.708
[sighs]

1:21:14.875 --> 1:21:16.458
Took you long enough.

1:21:16.541 --> 1:21:18.083
[Grace] I told you I was busy.

1:21:21.000 --> 1:21:23.333
Edem is not being straightforward with us.

1:21:23.791 --> 1:21:25.333
We need to find out what's going on.

1:21:25.416 --> 1:21:27.041
[Grace] Who cares what's going on?

1:21:29.166 --> 1:21:32.291
He's just a broke playboy
who wants to stay on the gravy train.

1:21:32.958 --> 1:21:36.791
Besides, I'm really confused
as to why you're concerned with that.

1:21:36.875 --> 1:21:40.166
Rather than being concerned with actual
children who are being poisoned

1:21:40.250 --> 1:21:42.375
-by a pharmaceutical company.
-Jesus!

1:21:42.458 --> 1:21:44.000
Why does this bother you so much?

1:21:44.083 --> 1:21:45.958
Why does it not bother you at all?

1:21:46.208 --> 1:21:47.166
Chike.

1:21:48.166 --> 1:21:49.416
In my research,

1:21:49.666 --> 1:21:53.500
I found out that the Eleshos once had
a three-year-old daughter who had died.

1:21:53.708 --> 1:21:54.833
I didn't think anything of it,

1:21:54.916 --> 1:21:58.166
until one of my clients and contacts
sent me this picture.

1:22:04.708 --> 1:22:05.708
Yeah, but--

1:22:06.041 --> 1:22:06.916
Shh.

1:22:15.875 --> 1:22:16.833
[gasps]

1:22:24.333 --> 1:22:26.666
[foreboding music]

1:22:30.833 --> 1:22:32.958
[water running]

1:22:49.791 --> 1:22:53.041
[Kelly] <i>You are not working with Madame
to hook Edem and Motunrayo up.</i>

1:22:53.416 --> 1:22:55.416
<i>They are planning to take over Daraja.</i>

1:22:55.500 --> 1:22:58.166
<i>They're using you to get the cooperation
of the US government</i>

1:22:58.250 --> 1:23:00.708
<i>in exchange for handing you over
for drug crimes.</i>

1:23:00.791 --> 1:23:03.333
<i>I've been trying to figure out
a way to get you out,</i>

1:23:03.416 --> 1:23:05.625
<i>but they've been watching me like a hawk.</i>

1:23:06.083 --> 1:23:07.541
<i>They pull the trigger tomorrow.</i>

1:23:07.625 --> 1:23:09.250
<i>We're out of options.</i>

1:23:09.750 --> 1:23:12.416
<i>I'm sorry,
I'm telling you this so you can run.</i>

1:23:37.833 --> 1:23:39.833
[gloomy music]

1:23:53.583 --> 1:23:55.500
[water running]

1:24:06.458 --> 1:24:08.666
[gloomy music]

1:24:23.000 --> 1:24:24.208
[Kelly] <i>We need to see.</i>

1:24:24.875 --> 1:24:28.583
<i>Go to Madame. Tell her that you need to go
over tomorrows plans with her and Mide,</i>

1:24:28.666 --> 1:24:30.416
<i>to ensure nothing goes wrong.</i>

1:24:30.500 --> 1:24:32.083
<i>Once he leaves, I'll leave.</i>

1:24:32.458 --> 1:24:34.666
<i>Once you are done with that
come meet me at the spot.</i>

1:24:34.958 --> 1:24:36.375
<i>Make sure you are not followed.</i>

1:24:37.500 --> 1:24:39.291
[water running]

1:24:40.708 --> 1:24:41.750
[water turns off]

1:24:47.291 --> 1:24:49.458
[gloomy music]

1:25:00.958 --> 1:25:02.541
Sorry, it took this long.

1:25:03.250 --> 1:25:05.875
Madame has been obsessively
preparing for tomorrow.

1:25:06.166 --> 1:25:07.583
How could you not tell me?

1:25:07.875 --> 1:25:11.000
Chike, I couldn't tell you
and then risk you blowing it.

1:25:11.458 --> 1:25:13.416
I spent the last three months
looking for how--

1:25:13.500 --> 1:25:15.500
And the best you could come up with
was run away?

1:25:16.041 --> 1:25:17.958
It's either that,
or you spend 20 years in jail

1:25:18.041 --> 1:25:20.416
-for drug crime...
-So what happens to you if I run?

1:25:20.500 --> 1:25:22.041
It'll be my turn to save you.

1:25:22.500 --> 1:25:24.958
Lucky me, but, no.

1:25:25.916 --> 1:25:26.958
No.

1:25:28.750 --> 1:25:30.125
So, what do we do?

1:25:31.041 --> 1:25:34.416
Madame will expect you
to confront her tomorrow about her child.

1:25:34.791 --> 1:25:37.125
And then Kelly is supposed
to come in and make an arrest.

1:25:37.208 --> 1:25:40.166
And if I run, they will know
that you tipped me off.

1:25:40.250 --> 1:25:41.291
[Grace] Yes.

1:25:44.375 --> 1:25:46.541
There is only one thing we can do.

1:25:47.875 --> 1:25:50.916
[Bamidele] Why wouldn't I just
confront Motunrayo and stop this?

1:25:51.000 --> 1:25:53.166
Because Madame will try again.

1:25:53.458 --> 1:25:56.041
It's better to let the plan go ahead
then counter it.

1:25:57.041 --> 1:25:57.875
[sighs]

1:25:57.958 --> 1:26:00.333
Are you sure this is not just a plan
for you to get away?

1:26:01.500 --> 1:26:03.083
The US is arresting me.

1:26:03.875 --> 1:26:07.041
The question you have to answer
is whether Madame goes down with me.

1:26:09.250 --> 1:26:11.458
[gloomy music]

1:26:13.583 --> 1:26:16.291
Did you not read the terms
of your immunity deal?

1:26:16.791 --> 1:26:19.291
We want to know what it will take
to change that deal.

1:26:22.458 --> 1:26:24.666
Grace, Grace, run, run! It's a trap.

1:26:25.541 --> 1:26:27.916
-It's a trap.
-Grace doesn't need to run.

1:26:28.708 --> 1:26:29.541
Grace?

1:26:29.625 --> 1:26:30.458
Yes, Madame.

1:26:30.541 --> 1:26:33.833
Hand the original surveillance footage
to Agent Spencer.

1:26:36.500 --> 1:26:37.833
You bitch.

1:26:38.250 --> 1:26:39.791
They were going to send
my mother to prison

1:26:39.875 --> 1:26:41.250
because of the money I sent to her.

1:26:41.333 --> 1:26:43.291
My fault, but I couldn't let that happen.

1:26:43.375 --> 1:26:45.041
You chose your mother over me?

1:26:48.041 --> 1:26:49.083
[grunts]

1:26:49.708 --> 1:26:51.708
[somber music]

1:27:03.250 --> 1:27:05.416
[somber music continues]

1:27:08.791 --> 1:27:11.625
[inaudible dialogue]

1:27:12.541 --> 1:27:14.458
[EKG monitor beeping]

1:27:15.375 --> 1:27:16.375
What?

1:27:17.458 --> 1:27:20.250
Oh, no, you're lying. No, you're lying.

1:27:20.458 --> 1:27:21.500
No!

1:27:22.708 --> 1:27:25.333
You, can you see that?

1:27:25.416 --> 1:27:26.875
This is all your fault!

1:27:26.958 --> 1:27:29.458
This is... This is all your fault!

1:27:30.250 --> 1:27:32.208
-This is all your fault!
-I know you're upset.

1:27:32.291 --> 1:27:34.416
You know... You know I'm upset. You...

1:27:34.875 --> 1:27:35.833
Fuck you!

1:27:35.916 --> 1:27:39.125
[speaking Yoruba]

1:27:39.208 --> 1:27:40.583
[in English]
But... but we can fix it.

1:27:40.875 --> 1:27:43.125
-So we can still fix it.
-We can fix...

1:27:43.208 --> 1:27:44.041
She's dead!

1:27:44.125 --> 1:27:45.750
Can you hear yourself? You can fix what?

1:27:46.625 --> 1:27:47.750
Leave me alone.

1:27:53.250 --> 1:27:54.291
[door closes]

1:27:56.333 --> 1:27:57.416
[sighs]

1:27:59.041 --> 1:28:00.500
[Chike] Grace, you need to calm him down.

1:28:00.583 --> 1:28:03.333
We need him on our side
to figure this thing out.

1:28:03.875 --> 1:28:06.333
Another impossible task coming up.

1:28:07.125 --> 1:28:10.833
Well, it looks like our deal is off
because you just lost your star witness.

1:28:10.916 --> 1:28:11.958
Wait.

1:28:12.041 --> 1:28:14.208
Our flight is at 6:00 a.m., right?

1:28:14.708 --> 1:28:15.750
[sighs]

1:28:15.833 --> 1:28:17.500
So I still have four hours.

1:28:19.375 --> 1:28:20.916
Or I could take you in.

1:28:22.166 --> 1:28:23.958
But maybe, our flight was now.

1:28:26.333 --> 1:28:29.125
Listen, I'm not going to stop you
at your chance of revenge, okay?

1:28:29.208 --> 1:28:31.750
But just know that the clock is ticking.

1:28:32.416 --> 1:28:33.458
Tick-tock.

1:28:43.625 --> 1:28:44.583
[sighs]

1:28:49.500 --> 1:28:51.625
[ominous music]

1:28:57.458 --> 1:28:59.750
[upbeat music playing]

1:29:08.166 --> 1:29:09.125
[Chike] Enitan.

1:29:09.958 --> 1:29:11.041
Enitan!

1:29:11.458 --> 1:29:14.083
You better get your green-eyed ass
down here now!

1:29:15.583 --> 1:29:17.750
The Americans are laxer than I thought.

1:29:17.833 --> 1:29:19.291
[Chike] I didn't escape.

1:29:19.833 --> 1:29:22.750
The Americans want me,
but I convinced them to take you too.

1:29:23.125 --> 1:29:26.708
Oh, and congratulations,
you got your revenge.

1:29:26.791 --> 1:29:28.083
Motunrayo is dead.

1:29:28.166 --> 1:29:29.250
[Edem] You're lying.

1:29:29.333 --> 1:29:31.000
[Chike] Is that guilt I hear?

1:29:31.708 --> 1:29:32.916
You should have thought about that

1:29:33.000 --> 1:29:35.000
before you got her
to betray her entire family

1:29:35.083 --> 1:29:36.583
for Madame's game.

1:29:36.666 --> 1:29:38.833
-She's lying.
-[Edem] Uh-uh. Obviously.

1:29:38.916 --> 1:29:40.416
You know, that day,

1:29:40.958 --> 1:29:42.250
in your house,

1:29:43.333 --> 1:29:44.958
I thought you were being real.

1:29:45.041 --> 1:29:46.375
[snickers]

1:29:47.416 --> 1:29:49.875
You were just telling her a sob story
so that she'll believe you.

1:29:49.958 --> 1:29:51.500
-Shut up!
-[Chike] And for what?

1:29:51.583 --> 1:29:53.458
So that Madame can own shares?

1:29:53.541 --> 1:29:55.583
Why are you trying to divide us?

1:29:56.125 --> 1:29:57.250
I have the golden share,

1:29:57.333 --> 1:29:59.833
and the plan has always been for Edem
to have some of my shares.

1:29:59.916 --> 1:30:00.875
[laughs]

1:30:01.041 --> 1:30:02.333
Point of correction.

1:30:02.875 --> 1:30:05.458
You think you have the golden share.

1:30:09.708 --> 1:30:11.916
[tense music]

1:30:21.125 --> 1:30:23.500
[tense music continues]

1:30:26.666 --> 1:30:27.916
[Edem] We have a problem.

1:30:28.291 --> 1:30:29.666
Chike has the golden share.

1:30:29.750 --> 1:30:31.333
The transaction is invalid.

1:30:31.958 --> 1:30:33.458
Are the agreements ready?

1:30:33.666 --> 1:30:34.875
Yes, Madame.

1:30:34.958 --> 1:30:37.125
They will all be ready
for the arrival of the elections.

1:30:39.583 --> 1:30:41.833
Get me that crazy girl!

1:30:54.416 --> 1:30:55.458
You...

1:30:56.083 --> 1:30:58.625
will sign the golden shares to me.

1:31:00.250 --> 1:31:01.375
Why would I?

1:31:01.458 --> 1:31:02.333
[thwacks]

1:31:03.416 --> 1:31:04.333
Huh.

1:31:06.875 --> 1:31:08.375
You still don't get it, do you?

1:31:09.833 --> 1:31:11.458
You could break me if you had time,

1:31:11.541 --> 1:31:13.125
but when Agent Spencer dropped me off,

1:31:13.208 --> 1:31:15.083
she gave me 30 minutes.

1:31:16.041 --> 1:31:18.958
Now I'm betting that I could hold off
for the remaining five minutes or so.

1:31:20.791 --> 1:31:23.416
That's a bet I'm willing to take.

1:31:23.666 --> 1:31:25.916
Wait. Just one second.

1:31:29.125 --> 1:31:30.750
This doesn't make sense.

1:31:32.708 --> 1:31:33.958
Why did you come back?

1:31:34.041 --> 1:31:35.416
I came back for you.

1:31:38.041 --> 1:31:40.541
Madame's share transfers are invalid.

1:31:40.625 --> 1:31:41.625
Hmm.

1:31:41.708 --> 1:31:43.666
Motunrayo still has all the shares.

1:31:44.583 --> 1:31:45.750
But she's dead.

1:31:46.291 --> 1:31:48.333
And Bamidele is her next of kin.

1:31:49.958 --> 1:31:53.125
Now he wants revenge on the woman
that killed his sister.

1:31:54.333 --> 1:31:56.708
He is willing to offer you
20 percent of Daraja

1:31:56.791 --> 1:31:59.375
if you confess your part in the scam
to the US government.

1:32:00.416 --> 1:32:01.916
You get immunity...

1:32:03.000 --> 1:32:04.541
and she goes to jail.

1:32:05.625 --> 1:32:06.583
You're lying.

1:32:06.666 --> 1:32:07.708
Check my purse.

1:32:08.041 --> 1:32:09.041
[snickers]

1:32:09.375 --> 1:32:10.541
Edem.

1:32:11.541 --> 1:32:13.208
There are two documents.

1:32:14.708 --> 1:32:16.500
A share transfer form...

1:32:17.166 --> 1:32:20.000
and an offer of immunity
from the US government.

1:32:23.541 --> 1:32:24.708
Edem!

1:32:25.416 --> 1:32:27.583
Well, they're signed.

1:32:28.125 --> 1:32:30.000
So, why do I need you?

1:32:30.083 --> 1:32:31.125
You don't.

1:32:33.125 --> 1:32:35.416
But how does Madame know
that you are not going to turn on her?

1:32:35.500 --> 1:32:36.416
[Madame] Edem.

1:32:36.500 --> 1:32:38.750
Tear that up!

1:32:38.833 --> 1:32:40.083
[Chike laughs]

1:32:43.875 --> 1:32:44.916
Wow!

1:32:45.458 --> 1:32:46.375
[Chike] Whoa!

1:32:47.333 --> 1:32:49.750
[tense music]

1:32:55.916 --> 1:32:58.500
I accept your deal!
[panting]

1:33:02.583 --> 1:33:04.750
[foreboding music]

1:33:06.166 --> 1:33:07.458
I could kill you right here.

1:33:08.166 --> 1:33:09.416
Right now.

1:33:09.500 --> 1:33:11.541
-No.
-[knife clanks]

1:33:11.791 --> 1:33:13.000
You couldn't.

1:33:15.166 --> 1:33:17.125
Is that all you have to say to me?

1:33:19.208 --> 1:33:21.291
You know, I...
I thought real hard and long

1:33:21.375 --> 1:33:22.625
about a speech...

1:33:24.000 --> 1:33:25.083
but nah.

1:33:25.708 --> 1:33:26.916
Fuck you!

1:33:27.791 --> 1:33:28.875
I won.

1:33:29.416 --> 1:33:30.333
Whoo!

1:33:31.916 --> 1:33:33.208
[Chike laughs]

1:33:33.958 --> 1:33:36.375
[gloomy music]

1:33:38.500 --> 1:33:40.250
[chair clanks]

